cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the efficiency of evolutionary algorithms for optimization problems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of different algorithmic restrictions on the efficiency of black-box optimization algorithms.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses information-theoretic considerations to derive lower bounds on the black-box complexity.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper analyzes the complexity of the OneMax function under different algorithmic restrictions.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the OneMax function is a classical set of test functions that is related to coin-weighing problems and the board game Mastermind.
